<definition-item><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">B42C7/00</classification-symbol><definition-title>Manufacturing bookbinding cases or covers of {books or} loose-leaf binders  (book covers <class-ref scheme="cpc">B42D3/00</class-ref>)</definition-title><definition-statement>
      <section-title>Definition statement</section-title>
      <section-body><paragraph-text type="preamble">This place covers:</paragraph-text>
        <paragraph-text type="body">Bookbinding cases are usually manufactured as a separate unit to be associated with the fillings of a book.</paragraph-text>
        <paragraph-text type="body">Cases for hard cover books, or covers for loose-leave binders, are typically produced by printing a rectangular sheet of paper, cloth or leather, known as the cover material, and subsequently gluing the cover material to a pair of rigid panels and a spine.</paragraph-text>
        <paragraph-text type="body">Soft covers, e.g. for books, folders (<class-ref scheme="cpc">B42F7/00</class-ref> etc.) or suspension files (<class-ref scheme="cpc">B42F15/00</class-ref>), are made from foldable sheet material, e.g. as unitary cover from a single printed blank of cover material.</paragraph-text>
